* Stage_Lock_Status

Relationship:

```
Tender
   ‚Üì
Bids
   ‚Üì
Opening Event
   ‚Üì
Disclosure Rules Applied
```

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£6Ô∏è‚É£ KPI METRICS

* On-time opening rate
* Opening irregularity incidents
* Technical-to-financial stage duration
* Disclosure compliance rate
* Integrity verification failures
* Audit findings frequency

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£7Ô∏è‚É£ COMMON FAILURE POINTS (TO DESIGN AGAINST)

‚ùå Early financial disclosure
‚ùå Single-person opening authority
‚ùå Weak encryption key storage
‚ùå Manual override without audit trail
‚ùå Lack of immutable opening report
‚ùå Uncontrolled visibility to unauthorized roles

System design must eliminate these risks.

---

# 1Ô∏è‚É£8Ô∏è‚É£ END-TO-END SUMMARY

Logic 7 ensures:

* Procedural correctness
* Controlled, stage-based disclosure
* Transparency without manipulation
* Enforced separation between technical and financial review
* Immutable opening records
* Multi-person governance control

It creates the secure transition between:

**Bid Submission (Logic 6)**
and
**Evaluation & Scoring (Logic 8)**

